title: Area rankings (10/19): DeSoto reenters Top 10, Terrell makes big jump
text:
On Thursday and Friday night, the only way to keep up with your team and games across the area is beta.SportsDayHS.com . Get live play-by-play and stats so you can get up-to-the-second updates directly on your phone. Find your game here and follow the action throughout Week 8.
CLASS 6A
On the rise: No. 10 DeSoto climbed six spots after its 48-31 win over then-No. 8 South Grand Prairie, rushing 49 times for 390 yards and six touchdowns in the game. DeSoto will face No. 3 Cedar Hill this week.

On the rise: No. 11 Frisco Wakeland rose seven spots after its 35-28 victory over Frisco Centennial. Junior RB Jay Orji rushed for 225 yards and five scores in the win, his sixth straight game with 140 or more yards and at least one touchdown.
